Observations (from mine limited position)
 
.- Geth and Besu eth_getTransactionByBlockNumberAndIndex do not returned the data field value, which as we can see is the same as the input field value. Nethermind returns both values.

.- Nethermind and Besu APIs access the node with the curl command: 

curl -k -s --data '{"method":"trace_block","params":["latest"],"id":1,"jsonrpc":"2.0"}' -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
-X POST https://api.archivenode.io/n21le9m5ogypuubc2hdh8n21le9vhv6n/nethermind

 geth: uses geth attach http://localhost:8545

.- Geth has an option for 
>geth attach http://localhost:8545 –exec "eth.getBlock('$block_number','1000')" 
to return or not the Transactions info for the block, please see the script above in geth section.

.- The data output structure presented for Block and Transaction traces is different between nethermind and geth, see examples.

.- Geth and Besu apparently return same data structure for each of the above API calls.
